{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Federal Institute for Geosciences and Natural Resources |nativename = Bundesanstalt für Geowissenschaften und Rohstoffe (BGR) |logo = Bundesanstalt_für_Geowissenschaften_und_Rohstoffe_Logo.svg |logo_width = |formed = |preceding1 = |preceding2 = |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = |headquarters = [[Hanover]], Germany |employees = 795 in 2013 |budget = |chief1_name = |chief1_position = |chief2_name = |parent_agency = |child2_agency = |website = [http://www.bgr.bund.de www.bgr.bund.de] |footnotes = }} The '''Federal Institute for Geosciences and Natural Resources''' ('''Bundesanstalt für Geowissenschaften und Rohstoffe''' or '''BGR''') is a German agency within the [[Federal Ministry of Economics and Technology]]. It acts as a central [[geoscience]] consulting institution for the [[German federal government]].<ref name=BGR-Home>{{cite web|title=BGR Homepage|url=http://www.bgr.bund.de/EN/Home/homepage_node_en.html|publisher=BGR|accessdate=20 May 2015}}</ref> The headquarters of the agency is located in [[Hanover]] and there is a branch in [[Berlin]]. Early 2013, the BGR employed a total of 795 employees. The BGR, the State Authority for Mining, Energy and Geology and the Leibniz Institute for Applied Geophysics form the Geozentrum Hanover. All three institutions have a common management and infrastructure, and complement each other through their interdisciplinary expertise. <gallery> File:Sitz in Hannover, BGR.jpg|Sitz in Hannover </gallery> == External links == * [http://www.bgr.bund.de/DE/Home/homepage_node.html Official BGR webpage]
